From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 12:10:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L32-L35: bytecode dispatch + execution reached

The interpreter now DISPATCHES and EXECUTES bytecode templates. Four
more layers, all variants of the codecache↔libjvm.so reach problem or
cap-tag stripping:

  L32: SkipIfEqual (global flag checks, e.g. DTraceMethodProbes) used
       PCC-relative adrp to a libjvm.so .bss global — unreachable from
       codecache (DDC is null in purecap, so a DDC+SCVALUE attempt also
       failed). These flags are parsed during JVM init, BEFORE the
       interpreter is generated, and constant after — so resolve the
       comparison at CODEGEN time and emit a static branch.

  L33: generate_fixed_frame computed rbcp = ConstMethod + codes_offset
       via integer add → tag-0 rbcp → the bytecode-dispatch ldrb[rbcp]!
       faulted. cap-ADD preserves the ConstMethod capability.

  L34: get_dispatch loaded the dispatch table via PCC-relative adrp; the
       table is a libjvm.so .bss global, so the address fell outside the
       codecache PCC's representable range and the tag cleared. Added
       Thread::_cap_dispatch, seeded in C++ (Thread ctor + re-seeded for
       the main thread in init_globals after interpreter_init), and
       get_dispatch now loads that tagged cap via rthread.

  L35: generate_fixed_frame computed esp (expression-stack pointer) via
       integer sub of sp → tag-0 esp → every bytecode template's
       [esp],#16 operand push/pop faulted. cap-SUB preserves the tag.

RESULT: dispatch works (we branch into the real template table), and
templates execute (observed the ixor template popping operands, then a
template calling a libjvm.so runtime helper). Crossed from "interpreter
prologue" into actual Java bytecode execution + runtime callbacks.

Also added the cap_lea_global helper (DDC+SCVALUE) — kept for reference
though SkipIfEqual uses the codegen-time approach instead — and a
DIAG abort-after-3 in the SIGPROT handler to break the
retry-without-advance loop on bounds (si_code=1) faults the handler
doesn't forward.

Next: a SIGILL in a template / a runtime fault, currently obscured by
the diagnostic sigill_handler taking a nested fault — to be cleaned up.

Session: 36 commits, 93 build iterations, layers L25-L35 resolved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

